20840,"EC research finds shutting down of pirate sites ineffective",http://torrentfreak.com/shutting-down-pirate-sites-is-ineffective-european-commission-finds-150514/?,"<p>New research from the European Commission’s <a href=""https://ec.europa.eu/jrc/"">Joint Research Centre</a> shows that shutting down pirate website such as The Pirate Bay is relatively ineffective and potentially counterproductive.</p><p>In the <a href=""http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=2604197"">working paper</a> entitled “Online Copyright Enforcement, Consumer Behavior, and Market Structure” researchers examined clickstream data to see how legal and illegal consumption habits changed in response to the shutdown. Results show a short-lived decrease in piracy (after which piracy levels return to normal) and only a small increase in the use of legal services.</p>",1,"2015-05-14 20:44:00",EU,ipr,"european-commission, working-document, pirate-websites, pirate-bay, joint-research-centre, illegal-consumption, shutdown, infringement, report, research, copyright",academia
