36895,"Safe Harbor annulled by the European Court of Justice",https://www.laquadrature.net/en/safe-harbor-repealed-cjue,"<p>By a decision <a href=""https://www.laquadrature.net//files/schrems_CJUE.pdf"">published this morning</a>, the Court of Justice of the European Union (CJEU), the highest European jurisdiction, repealed the Safe Harbor agreement. This agreement in effect since 2000, allows data transfers between Europe and the United States under different versions, authorised the processing of European citizens' data by US companies, with fewer guarantees than those existing in Europe.</p><p>Max Schrems, an Austrian citizen, has put Facebook on trial since the monitoring by the NSA of his data hosted by Facebook had an impact on his freedom and privacy. The CJEU today confirmed his viewpoint by invalidating the Safe Harbor and held that the European Commission abused its power by approving it. The CJEU also affirmed that a local data protection authority may dissent a European agreement if guarantees granted to citizens were modified.</p><!--break--><!--break--><div>&nbsp;</div><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>",1,"2015-10-06 16:40:12",EU,privacy,"cjeu, court-decision, internet, safe-harbor, european-commission, us, max-schrems, data-protection, data-transfer, agreement, surveillance, privacy",
