84155,"NIST framework for improving critical infrastructure cybersecurity",http://www.sbs.ox.ac.uk/cybersecurity-capacity/content/framework-improving-critical-infrastructure-cybersecurity,"<p>The Framework, which was created by the <a href=""http://www.nist.gov/"">National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST)</a> through collaboration between industry and government, consists of standards, guidelines, and practices to promote the protection of critical infrastructure. It uses a common language to address and manage cybersecurity risk in a cost-effective way based on business needs without placing additional regulatory requirements on businesses.</p><p>The Framework focuses on using business drivers to guide cybersecurity activities and considering cybersecurity risks as part of the organization’s risk management processes. It consists of three parts: the Framework Core, the Framework Profile, and the Framework Implementation Tiers.</p><p>The Framework can be downloaded <a href=""https://www.sbs.ox.ac.uk/cybersecurity-capacity/system/files/cybersecurity-framework-021214.pdf"">here</a>.</p>",1,"2016-10-24 21:20:19",Global,ig,"nist, guidelines, framework, cybersecurity, critical-infrastructure",government
